				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$(E_{\mathrm {T}},\eta )$$\end{document} bin, the level of background is evaluated by the use of sensitive discriminating variables to build templates able to provide some separation between signal and background events. These templates are then either fitted or normalised to data to evaluate and subtract the estimated background component in the signal sample.

